This paper is about evaluating enjoyment and flow in information visualization, which is a topic that falls under the sub-category of Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) and Visualization (cs.VIS). Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of enjoyment on performance and memorability, which relates to the sub-category of Cybersecurity (cs.CYBER). The paper also discusses previous work in the area of visualization evaluation, which falls under the sub-category of Graphics (cs.GR) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
